{"key":"post-11698279","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11698279</id>\n<content>We'd all be a lot healthier and diabetes would be virtually wiped out if people and corporations such as soft drink and cookie/pastry makers would swear off sugar and use honey instead.&amp;nbsp; We use it for everything from cooking/baking to sweetening coffee.&amp;nbsp; In fact, if I need a quick snack, I'll pour honey into the palm of my hand and eat it directly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The biggest problem is that 2/3 of all beehives have been wiped out in the last five or so years.&amp;nbsp; Bees can't tolerate constant exposure to pesticides, which when it doesn't kill them outright, weakens them to the point they can't defend themselves against parasitic mites.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I'm taking this thread a bit off-topic, but I fed my bees with spent shiitake blocks last summer, and noticed in the fall when I went to treat for mites, they didn't have any.&amp;nbsp; I suspect something in the shiitake killed the mites.&amp;nbsp; Next year, I'll investigate this farther.&amp;nbsp; It might be the cure for CCD.&amp;nbsp; I haven't lost a single hive to CCD, although 90% of beekeepers have.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11698316</next>\n<prev>11698198</prev>\n<first>11681761</first>\n<last>13673392</last>\n<when>1261506237</when>\n<utime>12/22/09 08:23 PM</utime>\n</post>"}